of-these-nazi-looted-masterpiecesand-could-displaying-them-at-one-of-frances-most-popular-museums-help-track-them-down-180988779/</link><description>奥赛博物馆的一个新的永久展览展示了二战期间可能被盗或在可疑情况下被出售的艺术品。官员们仍然希望找到其合法主人的家人</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 15:02:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/who-are-the-owners-of-these-nazi-looted-masterpiecesand-could-displaying-them-at-one-of-frances-most-popular-museums-help-track-them-down-180988779/</guid></item><item><title>突破性的 DNA 分析鉴定出马里兰殖民地最早定居者的 130 万在世亲属</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/groundbreaking-dna-analysis-identifies-13-million-living-relatives-of-colonial-marylands-earliest-settlers-180988778/</link><description>专家将埋在圣玛丽市墓地的 49 具骸骨的 DNA 与 1150 万 23andMe 用户共享的基因数据进行了比较。他们还确定了可能是该殖民地第二任总督的遗骸</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 14:49:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/groundbreaking-dna-analysis-identifies-13-million-living-relatives-of-colonial-marylands-earliest-settlers-180988778/</guid></item><item><title>一项研究表明，地中海僧海豹在繁忙的夏季隐藏在水下“气泡洞”中以避免游客</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mediterranean-monk-seals-hide-in-underwater-bubble-caves-to-avoid-tourists-during-the-busy-summer-season-a-study-suggests-180988775/</link><description>研究人员在希腊福米库拉岛上的一个僻静的房间里发现了这种罕见的鳍足类动物正在休息和睡觉。研究结果表明，这些小洞穴应该被纳入保护动物栖息地的努力中</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 14:40:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mediterranean-monk-seals-hide-in-underwater-bubble-caves-to-avoid-tourists-during-the-busy-summer-season-a-study-suggests-180988775/</guid></item><item><title>加拿大这座矿井每年可能会释放出足够的天然氢来为 400 户家庭供电，这暗示着清洁能源尚未开发的来源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-canadian-mine-might-release-enough-natural-hydrogen-each-year-to-power-400-homes-hinting-at-an-untapped-source-of-clean-energy-180988773/</link><description>该国的许多金属矿山都埋藏在古老的岩层中，该岩层可能还蕴藏着大量被称为“白氢”的资源</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-canadian-mine-might-release-enough-natural-hydrogen-each-year-to-power-400-homes-hinting-at-an-untapped-source-of-clean-energy-180988773/</guid></item><item><title>发现的一批骨头和牙齿为老挝百年之谜“死亡罐子”提供了新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-discovered-trove-of-bones-and-teeth-yields-new-clues-to-the-century-old-mystery-of-death-jars-in-laos-180988772/</link><description>科学家们在东南亚最令人费解的考古遗址之一的一个巨大石罐里发现了 37 具骨头。这一发现表明了多代人的埋葬方式</description><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 21:08:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-discovered-trove-of-bones-and-teeth-yields-new-clues-to-the-century-old-mystery-of-death-jars-in-laos-180988772/</guid></item><item><title>考古学家从德国的一个中世纪厕所中取出了一本原始的皮革笔记本，其中保存了几个世纪以来的拉丁草书</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/from-a-medieval-latrine-in-germany-archaeologists-extracted-a-pristine-leather-notebook-that-preserved-latin-cursive-for-centuries-180988771/</link><description>小册子上的文字表明它属于一位上层商人，他可能在 800 年前使用厕所时发生了事故</description><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 19:11:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/from-a-medieval-latrine-in-germany-archaeologists-extracted-a-pristine-leather-notebook-that-preserved-latin-cursive-for-centuries-180988771/</guid></item><item><title>科学家表示，巴布亚企鹅实际上是四种不同的物种，这表明它们毕竟不是气候变化的“赢家”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gentoo-penguins-may-actually-be-four-different-species-scientists-say-revealing-theyre-not-quite-winners-of-climate-change-after-all-180988769/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，随着时间的推移，随着孤立的种群发生变化以适应其环境条件，适应性强的鸟类进化成不同的谱系。这项工作对自然资源保护主义者如何评估巴布亚蜥蜴的威胁具有重要意义</description><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 19:09:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gentoo-penguins-may-actually-be-four-different-species-scientists-say-revealing-theyre-not-quite-winners-of-climate-change-after-all-180988769/</guid></item></channel></rss>